{
  "video_id": "1vm3od_UmFg",
  "title": "The DNA Double Helix Discovery â€” HHMI BioInteractive Video",
  "es": 1,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 14100.0,
      "end_time": 16834.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] In the early   twentieth century, physicists"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 16834.0,
      "end_time": 19634.0,
      "text": "and chemists unlocked   secrets of the atom"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 19634.0,
      "end_time": 24767.0,
      "text": "that changed the world forever."
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 24767.0,
      "end_time": 27267.0,
      "text": "But life remained   a profound mystery."
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 27267.0,
      "end_time": 31901.0,
      "text": "Among life&#39;s deepest   secrets was inheritance."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 31901.0,
      "end_time": 34501.0,
      "text": "Everyone knew that traits   like the shape of a peapod"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 34501.0,
      "end_time": 36701.0,
      "text": "or the color of eyes   and hair were passed"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 36701.0,
      "end_time": 39200.0,
      "text": "on from generation   to generation."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 39200.0,
      "end_time": 40133.0,
      "text": "But no one knew how"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 40133.0,
      "end_time": 43634.0,
      "text": "such information was   stored or transmitted."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 43634.0,
      "end_time": 45200.0,
      "text": "Scientists were convinced   that there had"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 45200.0,
      "end_time": 47567.0,
      "text": "to be a biological molecule   at the heart of the process."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 47567.0,
      "end_time": 51400.0,
      "text": "And that molecule had to have   some pretty special qualities."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 51400.0,
      "end_time": 53300.0,
      "text": "[CARROLL:] The three   dimensional arrangement of atoms"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 53300.0,
      "end_time": 56501.0,
      "text": "in those molecules had to   explain the stability of life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 56501.0,
      "end_time": 58767.0,
      "text": "so that traits were passed   faithfully from generation"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 58767.0,
      "end_time": 61968.0,
      "text": "to generation, and also   the mutability of life."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 61968.0,
      "end_time": 66000.0,
      "text": "You have to have change in   order for evolution to happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 66000.0,
      "end_time": 66601.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The challenge"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 66601.0,
      "end_time": 69267.0,
      "text": "of solving this mysterious   arrangement of atoms,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 69267.0,
      "end_time": 73267.0,
      "text": "this fundamental &quot;secret of   life,&quot; was taken up in 1951"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 73267.0,
      "end_time": 75734.0,
      "text": "by two unknown scientists."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 75734.0,
      "end_time": 78033.0,
      "text": "Less than 18 months   later, they would make one"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 78033.0,
      "end_time": 87367.0,
      "text": "of the great discoveries   of the twentieth century."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 87367.0,
      "end_time": 90000.0,
      "text": "They met and joined forces   at the Cavendish laboratory"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 90000.0,
      "end_time": 92033.0,
      "text": "in Cambridge, England."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 92033.0,
      "end_time": 96200.0,
      "text": "One was a 23-year-old   American named James Watson."
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 96200.0,
      "end_time": 98501.0,
      "text": "[OLBY:] He had a crew cut when   he first came to Cambridge,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 98501.0,
      "end_time": 101567.0,
      "text": "and that was very rare in   Cambridge in those days."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 101567.0,
      "end_time": 104234.0,
      "text": "He liked to wear   what I call gym shoes"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 104234.0,
      "end_time": 106601.0,
      "text": "and leave the laces untied   and things like that."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 106601.0,
      "end_time": 110534.0,
      "text": "He was quite an enfant   terrible I would say."
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 110534.0,
      "end_time": 114634.0,
      "text": "But behind that, of course,   was his extreme, intense love"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 114634.0,
      "end_time": 119234.0,
      "text": "of science right from his early   years, and his determination."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 119234.0,
      "end_time": 121868.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The other was an   Englishman named Francis Crick."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 121868.0,
      "end_time": 123033.0,
      "text": "Trained as a physicist,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 123033.0,
      "end_time": 125701.0,
      "text": "his academic career had been   interrupted by the outbreak"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 125701.0,
      "end_time": 126767.0,
      "text": "of the Second World War."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 126767.0,
      "end_time": 131534.0,
      "text": "It wasn&#39;t until 1949 that he   got back into academic science."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 131534.0,
      "end_time": 133767.0,
      "text": "He was anxious to   make up for lost time"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 133767.0,
      "end_time": 137334.0,
      "text": "and now interested in biology."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 137334.0,
      "end_time": 141334.0,
      "text": "Crick and Watson connected   instantly when they met in 1951."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 141334.0,
      "end_time": 143801.0,
      "text": "They both loved to talk science."
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 143801.0,
      "end_time": 147734.0,
      "text": "[WATSON:] Francis and   I both liked ideas."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 147734.0,
      "end_time": 152067.0,
      "text": "And as long as I could talk to   Francis, I, you know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 152067.0,
      "end_time": 154334.0,
      "text": "felt every day   was worthwhile."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 154334.0,
      "end_time": 156634.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] Crick was always   ready to share his thoughts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 156634.0,
      "end_time": 158567.0,
      "text": "though he rarely did so quietly."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 158567.0,
      "end_time": 160634.0,
      "text": "[WATSON:] Any room he   was in he was going"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 160634.0,
      "end_time": 164734.0,
      "text": "to make more noise   than anyone else."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 164734.0,
      "end_time": 167033.0,
      "text": "[LUGER:] They would constantly   throw crazy ideas at each other,"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 167033.0,
      "end_time": 171834.0,
      "text": "dismiss them, have another idea,   follow that a little further,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 171834.0,
      "end_time": 174734.0,
      "text": "dismiss that, but then something   comes out of left field,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 174734.0,
      "end_time": 177133.0,
      "text": "so it&#39;s kind of this   give-and-take."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 177133.0,
      "end_time": 178534.0,
      "text": "[CRICK:] We did have   different backgrounds,"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 178534.0,
      "end_time": 181167.0,
      "text": "but we had the same interests."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 181167.0,
      "end_time": 183167.0,
      "text": "We... we both thought   that finding the structure"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 183167.0,
      "end_time": 184934.0,
      "text": "of the gene   was the key problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 184934.0,
      "end_time": 186467.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The idea of   the gene dates back"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 186467.0,
      "end_time": 189734.0,
      "text": "to Gregor Mendel&#39;s experiments   with pea plants in the 1860s."
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 189734.0,
      "end_time": 193734.0,
      "text": "By the 1920s, genes had been   convincingly located inside the"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 193734.0,
      "end_time": 195701.0,
      "text": "nucleus of cells, and associated"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 195701.0,
      "end_time": 197834.0,
      "text": "with structures called   chromosomes."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 197834.0,
      "end_time": 199601.0,
      "text": "It was also known that   chromosomes are made"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 199601.0,
      "end_time": 206234.0,
      "text": "of proteins, and a nucleic acid,   deoxyribonucleic acid, or DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 206234.0,
      "end_time": 211000.0,
      "text": "That meant that genes had to be   made of either DNA or protein."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 211000.0,
      "end_time": 212667.0,
      "text": "But which was it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 212667.0,
      "end_time": 214667.0,
      "text": "Protein seemed the better bet."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 214667.0,
      "end_time": 217167.0,
      "text": "There are lots of different   kinds of them and they do lots"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 217167.0,
      "end_time": 219234.0,
      "text": "of different stuff   inside the cell."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 219234.0,
      "end_time": 222901.0,
      "text": "In contrast, DNA didn&#39;t   seem very interesting."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 222901.0,
      "end_time": 226334.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s just repeated units of   a sugar linked to a phosphate"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 226334.0,
      "end_time": 229033.0,
      "text": "and any of four bases."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 229033.0,
      "end_time": 232133.0,
      "text": "The readiness to dismiss   DNA was so entrenched"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 232133.0,
      "end_time": 234934.0,
      "text": "that it persisted even   after Oswald Avery showed"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 234934.0,
      "end_time": 238501.0,
      "text": "that it can carry   genetic information."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 238501.0,
      "end_time": 241601.0,
      "text": "[CARROLL:] Avery had isolated a   substance that conveyed a trait"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 241601.0,
      "end_time": 243701.0,
      "text": "from one bacterium to another."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 243701.0,
      "end_time": 246534.0,
      "text": "And this &quot;transforming   principle,&quot; as he called it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 246534.0,
      "end_time": 248467.0,
      "text": "he showed that it   was not destroyed"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 248467.0,
      "end_time": 251934.0,
      "text": "by a protein-digesting   enzyme but was destroyed"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 251934.0,
      "end_time": 254133.0,
      "text": "by a DNA-digesting enzyme."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 254133.0,
      "end_time": 255667.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] Watson and   Crick were among the few"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 255667.0,
      "end_time": 257934.0,
      "text": "who found Avery&#39;s   work persuasive."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 257934.00000000003,
      "end_time": 260334.00000000003,
      "text": "They thought genes   were made of DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 260334.0,
      "end_time": 262501.0,
      "text": "They also thought that   solving the molecular structure"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 262501.0,
      "end_time": 265868.0,
      "text": "of the molecule would reveal how   genetic information is stored"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 265868.0,
      "end_time": 267834.0,
      "text": "and passed on."
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 267834.0,
      "end_time": 269567.0,
      "text": "At the time, a powerful   technique"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 269567.0,
      "end_time": 272334.0,
      "text": "for solving molecular   structure was being perfected:"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 272334.0,
      "end_time": 274834.0,
      "text": "x-ray crystallography."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 274834.0,
      "end_time": 275501.0,
      "text": "[LUGER:] At its best,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 275501.0,
      "end_time": 278133.0,
      "text": "x-ray crystallography can   determine the position"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 278133.0,
      "end_time": 281934.0,
      "text": "of every single atom in the   molecule that you&#39;re analyzing"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 281934.0,
      "end_time": 284934.0,
      "text": "with respect to every   other single atom."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 284934.0,
      "end_time": 286234.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] Not that it&#39;s easy."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 286234.0,
      "end_time": 289601.0,
      "text": "The picture you end up with   is a &quot;diffraction pattern,&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 289601.0,
      "end_time": 293300.0,
      "text": "and to make sense of it--to   work out where the atoms are--"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 293300.0,
      "end_time": 297234.0,
      "text": "involves interpreting   lengthy calculations."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 297234.0,
      "end_time": 299801.0,
      "text": "And in the 1950s, the   equipment was primitive"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 299801.0,
      "end_time": 301701.0,
      "text": "and difficult to maintain."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 301701.0,
      "end_time": 304000.0,
      "text": "The x-ray sources   weren&#39;t very bright."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 304000.0,
      "end_time": 307834.0,
      "text": "And on top of that, DNA is not   an easy molecule to work with."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 307834.0,
      "end_time": 309300.0,
      "text": "[LUGER:] Basically,   you picture snot."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 309300.0,
      "end_time": 312067.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s kind of hard to   pick it up and do stuff"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 312067.0,
      "end_time": 313634.0,
      "text": "with it, and analyze it."
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 313634.0,
      "end_time": 317834.0,
      "text": "Polymers are not fun to work   with from that point of view."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 317834.0,
      "end_time": 318968.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The Cavendish   was famous"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 318968.0,
      "end_time": 320968.0,
      "text": "for x-ray crystallography."
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 320968.0,
      "end_time": 323400.0,
      "text": "But the director of the   lab didn&#39;t want his staff"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 323400.0,
      "end_time": 324033.0,
      "text": "x-raying DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 324033.0,
      "end_time": 326901.0,
      "text": "He knew that a group   at King&#39;s College"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 326901.0,
      "end_time": 329767.0,
      "text": "in London was already doing   that and he didn&#39;t want"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 329767.0,
      "end_time": 331934.0,
      "text": "to be seen as competing."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 331934.0,
      "end_time": 334901.0,
      "text": "[WATSON:] It just wasn&#39;t..."
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 334901.0,
      "end_time": 337133.0,
      "text": "good manners."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 337133.0,
      "end_time": 338400.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The King&#39;s   College scientist"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 338400.0,
      "end_time": 342567.0,
      "text": "who had initiated the work   on DNA was Maurice Wilkins."
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 342567.0,
      "end_time": 345167.0,
      "text": "Like Crick, he was   trained as a physicist"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 345167.0,
      "end_time": 346934.0,
      "text": "and had only recently   become interested"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 346934.0,
      "end_time": 349267.0,
      "text": "in biological questions."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 349267.0,
      "end_time": 351567.0,
      "text": "Though he was drawn to   the problem of the gene,"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 351567.0,
      "end_time": 352834.0,
      "text": "Wilkins lacked Watson"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 352834.0,
      "end_time": 356901.0,
      "text": "and Crick&#39;s burning   urgency to find a solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 356901.0,
      "end_time": 359767.0,
      "text": "Complicating things for   Wilkins was his relationship"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 359767.0,
      "end_time": 362100.0,
      "text": "with his colleague   Rosalind Franklin."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 362100.0,
      "end_time": 364067.0,
      "text": "She was a talented   crystallographer,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 364067.0,
      "end_time": 366901.0,
      "text": "but when she joined the   team at Kings she believed"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 366901.0,
      "end_time": 369634.0,
      "text": "that she would be   leading its DNA research."
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 369634.0,
      "end_time": 371567.0,
      "text": "[LUGER:] She had the notion   that this was her project,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 371567.0,
      "end_time": 374534.0,
      "text": "he had the notion it was his   project, and if anything,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 374534.0,
      "end_time": 378501.0,
      "text": "she should help him in his   effort to solve the structure,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 378501.0,
      "end_time": 381467.0,
      "text": "and so this is a   recipe for disaster."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 381467.0,
      "end_time": 383868.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The times and   their personalities worked"
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 383868.0,
      "end_time": 386734.0,
      "text": "against an effective   partnership."
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 386734.0,
      "end_time": 389534.0,
      "text": "[LUGER:] This was a time when   it was very, very hard for women"
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 389534.0,
      "end_time": 394300.0,
      "text": "in science to be taken   seriously and so I would imagine"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 394300.0,
      "end_time": 398667.0,
      "text": "that Rosalind Franklin had to   be perhaps quite assertive."
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 398667.0,
      "end_time": 402234.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] She certainly   asserted her independence."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 402234.0,
      "end_time": 406234.0,
      "text": "Wilkins, by all accounts a   shy man, reluctantly agreed"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 406234.0,
      "end_time": 409501.0,
      "text": "that they would work separately."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 409501.0,
      "end_time": 413033.0,
      "text": "London is only 75   miles from Cambridge."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 413033.0,
      "end_time": 415501.0,
      "text": "That means that Watson and   Crick could easily keep tabs"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 415501.0,
      "end_time": 418033.0,
      "text": "on the work being done at Kings."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 418033.0,
      "end_time": 420133.0,
      "text": "But another potential   competitor was thousands"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 420133.0,
      "end_time": 423534.0,
      "text": "of miles away, in California."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 423534.0,
      "end_time": 424968.0,
      "text": "Linus Pauling was renowned"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 424968.0,
      "end_time": 427567.0,
      "text": "as the greatest physical   chemist of his generation."
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 427567.0,
      "end_time": 429834.0,
      "text": "He was widely admired   for his ability"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 429834.0,
      "end_time": 434701.0,
      "text": "to build accurate models   of complex molecules."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 434701.0,
      "end_time": 437000.0,
      "text": "Watson and Crick were   convinced it was just a matter"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 437000.0,
      "end_time": 442634.0,
      "text": "of time before Pauling used   this technique to solve DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 442634.0,
      "end_time": 446000.0,
      "text": "Biological molecules come   in a variety of shapes."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 446000.0,
      "end_time": 448234.0,
      "text": "Pauling, and Watson and Crick,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 448234.0,
      "end_time": 451334.0,
      "text": "suspected DNA might be   a helix of some kind."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 451334.0,
      "end_time": 454200.0,
      "text": "But if so, how were the   sugar, the phosphate"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 454200.0,
      "end_time": 456767.0,
      "text": "and the bases arranged?"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 456767.0,
      "end_time": 459667.0,
      "text": "Early in his collaboration   with Watson, Crick had worked"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 459667.0,
      "end_time": 462300.0,
      "text": "out mathematically what the   x-ray diffraction pattern"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 462300.0,
      "end_time": 465501.0,
      "text": "of a helical molecule   should look like."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 465501.0,
      "end_time": 468133.0,
      "text": "Shortly afterwards,   Watson went to London"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 468133.0,
      "end_time": 470334.0,
      "text": "to hear Franklin report on   some of her recent work."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 470334.0,
      "end_time": 475033.0,
      "text": "When he got back, he told Crick   what he remembered of her talk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 475033.0,
      "end_time": 477868.0,
      "text": "and they decided   to build a model."
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 477868.0,
      "end_time": 480200.0,
      "text": "In a few days, they had one."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 480200.0,
      "end_time": 483234.0,
      "text": "It was a helix, with three   sugar-phosphate chains"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 483234.0,
      "end_time": 486601.0,
      "text": "on the inside, and the   bases sticking out."
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 486601.0,
      "end_time": 488501.0,
      "text": "[LUGER:] At that time the   only interesting thing"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 488501.0,
      "end_time": 491300.0,
      "text": "about the DNA molecule   is the bases."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 491300.0,
      "end_time": 493868.0,
      "text": "And so it made perfect   sense, I mean,"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 493868.0,
      "end_time": 495634.0,
      "text": "only an idiot would   put them inside"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 495634.0,
      "end_time": 497534.0,
      "text": "because then they&#39;re hidden."
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 497534.0,
      "end_time": 499534.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] They invited   Wilkins and Franklin"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 499534.0,
      "end_time": 501467.0,
      "text": "to come and take a look."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 501467.0,
      "end_time": 504234.0,
      "text": "Unfortunately, Watson   had misremembered some"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 504234.0,
      "end_time": 505667.0,
      "text": "of her key measurements."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 505667.0,
      "end_time": 508501.0,
      "text": "Franklin saw this   immediately, and quickly"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 508501.0,
      "end_time": 511267.0,
      "text": "and derisively dismissed   their effort."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 511267.0,
      "end_time": 513334.0,
      "text": "She went to craft a   mocking announcement"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 513333.99999999994,
      "end_time": 517266.99999999994,
      "text": "for the death of DNA as a helix."
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 517267.00000000006,
      "end_time": 519834.00000000006,
      "text": "It was an embarrassment   that did not sit well"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 519833.99999999994,
      "end_time": 521233.99999999994,
      "text": "with the Cavendish leadership."
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 521234.00000000006,
      "end_time": 525234.0,
      "text": "[WATSON:] We were forbidden   in a sense to work on DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 525234.0,
      "end_time": 527901.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The failure of   the first model was painful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 527901.0,
      "end_time": 531367.0,
      "text": "but it can also be seen as just   part of the scientific process."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 531367.0,
      "end_time": 533367.0,
      "text": "[LUGER:] I would   actually maintain that,"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 533367.0,
      "end_time": 538434.0,
      "text": "in order to arrive at the   right solution, you have to put"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 538434.0,
      "end_time": 540601.0,
      "text": "out a couple of wrong ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 540601.0,
      "end_time": 544501.0,
      "text": "And that&#39;s just the nature of   discovery, and if you&#39;re afraid"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 544501.0,
      "end_time": 550534.0,
      "text": "of making a mistake, you&#39;re   going to fail in this business."
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 550534.0,
      "end_time": 554300.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] Through 1952, Watson   and Crick read and talked"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 554300.0,
      "end_time": 558033.0,
      "text": "over anything and everything   that could prove relevant"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 558033.0,
      "end_time": 560901.0,
      "text": "for their ongoing--   but now underground--"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 560901.0,
      "end_time": 563801.0,
      "text": "quest to discover   the structure of DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 563801.0,
      "end_time": 567701.0,
      "text": "[WATSON:] To me there was only   one way I could be happy..."
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 567701.0,
      "end_time": 572300.0,
      "text": "or two ways, you know: solve   DNA or get a girlfriend..."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 572300.0,
      "end_time": 580367.0,
      "text": "[laughs] and I didn&#39;t get a   girlfriend, so it was solve DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 580367.0,
      "end_time": 582601.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The year ended with   Watson and Crick thinking"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 582601.0,
      "end_time": 586534.0,
      "text": "about DNA, Franklin   taking pictures of DNA,"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 586534.0,
      "end_time": 590634.0,
      "text": "Wilkins avoiding Franklin,   and Pauling a distant"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 590634.0,
      "end_time": 592567.0,
      "text": "but worrisome presence."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 592567.0,
      "end_time": 597334.0,
      "text": "Then, in January 1953,   everything changed."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 597334.0,
      "end_time": 601000.0,
      "text": "News came that Pauling was   indeed preparing a paper"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 601000.0,
      "end_time": 602868.0,
      "text": "on the structure of DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 602868.0,
      "end_time": 605334.0,
      "text": "Watson secured a copy   of the manuscript."
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 605334.0,
      "end_time": 607434.0,
      "text": "And found, to his great relief,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 607434.0,
      "end_time": 609868.0,
      "text": "that Pauling was   proposing a triple helix."
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 609868.0,
      "end_time": 611534.0,
      "text": "It was very similar   to the one that he"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 611534.0,
      "end_time": 615567.0,
      "text": "and Crick had been shamed into   abandoning the previous year."
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 615567.0,
      "end_time": 617767.0,
      "text": "Relieved, he headed to   London to share the news"
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 617767.0,
      "end_time": 620567.0,
      "text": "that the race for   DNA wasn&#39;t over."
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 620567.0,
      "end_time": 623000.0,
      "text": "Only to find that Rosalind   Franklin wasn&#39;t particularly"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 623000.0,
      "end_time": 625067.0,
      "text": "interested in what   he had to say."
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 625067.0,
      "end_time": 627133.0,
      "text": "[OLBY:] Following his departure"
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 627133.0,
      "end_time": 631534.0,
      "text": "from Rosalind Franklin&#39;s   room he encountered Wilkins,"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 631534.0,
      "end_time": 634100.0,
      "text": "and Wilkins took him into   his room and then took"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 634100.0,
      "end_time": 636934.0,
      "text": "out of a drawer a picture"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 636934.0,
      "end_time": 639334.0,
      "text": "which had been taken   by Rosalind Franklin."
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 639334.0,
      "end_time": 641334.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] That picture   would become one"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 641334.0,
      "end_time": 648400.0,
      "text": "of the most famous images in all   biology: Franklin&#39;s Photo 51."
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 648400.0,
      "end_time": 650334.0,
      "text": "Jim Watson recognized   the diffraction pattern"
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 650334.0,
      "end_time": 653267.0,
      "text": "immediately-- it was a helix."
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 653267.0,
      "end_time": 654834.0,
      "text": "And based on this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 654834.0,
      "end_time": 659267.0,
      "text": "Watson thought it might have   just two chains: a double helix."
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 659267.0,
      "end_time": 664234.0,
      "text": "About the same time, Francis   Crick was shown a report"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 664234.0,
      "end_time": 667133.0,
      "text": "on Franklin&#39;s work that   included an observation"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 667133.0,
      "end_time": 669734.0,
      "text": "on the symmetry of DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 669734.0,
      "end_time": 671667.0,
      "text": "This led Crick to   a crucial insight"
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 671667.0,
      "end_time": 675367.0,
      "text": "that Franklin had missed:   the two backbones had to run"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 675367.0,
      "end_time": 677701.0,
      "text": "in opposite directions."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 677701.0,
      "end_time": 679300.0,
      "text": "That led him to the conclusion"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 679300.0,
      "end_time": 681234.0,
      "text": "that the sugar-phosphate   backbones had to be"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 681234.0,
      "end_time": 684901.0,
      "text": "on the outside with   the bases inside."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 684901.0,
      "end_time": 687901.0,
      "text": "So Watson started to   build models again."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 687901.0,
      "end_time": 690467.0,
      "text": "He experimented with   pairing like-with-like:"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 690467.0,
      "end_time": 694334.0,
      "text": "adenine with adenine, thymine   with thymine, and so on."
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 694334.0,
      "end_time": 696667.0,
      "text": "That would make each   chain identical."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 696667.0,
      "end_time": 699400.0,
      "text": "Watson thought that could   explain how genetic information"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 699400.0,
      "end_time": 701033.0,
      "text": "is stored."
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 701033.0,
      "end_time": 702868.0,
      "text": "He thought he had the solution."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 702868.0,
      "end_time": 706901.0,
      "text": "But then a Cambridge   colleague told him"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 706901.0,
      "end_time": 710267.0,
      "text": "that the bases could not pair   with themselves in that way."
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 710267.0,
      "end_time": 713300.0,
      "text": "And Crick pointed out that   the model didn&#39;t take account"
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 713300.0,
      "end_time": 716334.0,
      "text": "of something else that   was known about DNA."
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 716334.0,
      "end_time": 720133.0,
      "text": "A few years earlier, another   chemist interested in DNA,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 720133.0,
      "end_time": 723100.0,
      "text": "Erwin Chargaff, had   reported a puzzling fact"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 723100.0,
      "end_time": 724434.0,
      "text": "about the molecule."
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 724434.0,
      "end_time": 727000.0,
      "text": "[LUGER:] He analyzed the   chemical composition of DNA"
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 727000.0,
      "end_time": 732067.0,
      "text": "in different species and what he   found is that the amount of As,"
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 732067.0,
      "end_time": 737434.0,
      "text": "the base adenine, and the amount   of base Ts, was always the same."
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 737434.0,
      "end_time": 740334.0,
      "text": "And Gs and Cs were   always the same."
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 740334.0,
      "end_time": 742767.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] But no one,   including Chargaff,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 742767.0,
      "end_time": 745834.0,
      "text": "had figured out what   those base ratios meant."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 745834.0,
      "end_time": 748968.0,
      "text": "With Chargaff&#39;s data in   mind, Jim Watson went alone"
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 748968.0,
      "end_time": 751868.0,
      "text": "to the lab one Saturday   morning and started playing"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 751868.0,
      "end_time": 754634.0,
      "text": "with cardboard cutouts."
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 754634.0,
      "end_time": 756601.0,
      "text": "[WATSON:] I began   moving them around."
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 756601.0,
      "end_time": 760434.0,
      "text": "And I wanted an arrangement,   you know, where I had a big"
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 760434.0,
      "end_time": 765934.0,
      "text": "and a small molecule, and,   uh, so how did you do it?"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 765934.0,
      "end_time": 770834.0,
      "text": "Somehow you had to   form link bonds."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 770834.0,
      "end_time": 778067.0,
      "text": "So, here&#39;s an A and here&#39;s   T, and I wanted this hydrogen"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 778067.0,
      "end_time": 780467.0,
      "text": "to point directly   at this nitrogen,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 780467.0,
      "end_time": 782634.0,
      "text": "so I had something like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 782634.0,
      "end_time": 786901.0,
      "text": "Oh! So then I went   to the other pair"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 786901.0,
      "end_time": 789801.0,
      "text": "and I wanted this nitrogen   to point to this one."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 789801.0,
      "end_time": 791434.0,
      "text": "And it went like this."
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 791434.0,
      "end_time": 793634.0,
      "text": "Whoa! They looked the same."
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 793634.0,
      "end_time": 803067.0,
      "text": "And you can put one right   on top of the other."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 803067.0,
      "end_time": 811133.0,
      "text": "[music plays]"
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 811133.0,
      "end_time": 812467.0,
      "text": "We knew we could just..."
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 812467.0,
      "end_time": 814367.0,
      "text": "even if we go up to the ceiling,"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 814367.0,
      "end_time": 820634.0,
      "text": "we&#39;re building a tiny   fraction of the molecule."
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 820634.0,
      "end_time": 826334.0,
      "text": "Hundreds of millions of these   base pairs in one molecule,"
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 826334.0,
      "end_time": 829133.0,
      "text": "all fitting into this   wonderful symmetry"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 829133.0,
      "end_time": 837067.0,
      "text": "which we saw the morning   of February 28, 1953."
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 837067.0,
      "end_time": 838501.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The model   fit the measurements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 838501.0,
      "end_time": 840701.0,
      "text": "both from the x-ray   diffraction pictures"
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 840701.0,
      "end_time": 843000.0,
      "text": "and from Chargaff&#39;s data."
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 843000.0,
      "end_time": 845367.0,
      "text": "But most important of   all, the arrangement"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 845367.0,
      "end_time": 849400.0,
      "text": "of the bases immediately   revealed how DNA works."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 849400.0,
      "end_time": 850467.0,
      "text": "[CRICK:] The key aspect"
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 850467.0,
      "end_time": 853100.0,
      "text": "of the structure was   the complementary nature"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 853100.0,
      "end_time": 854100.0,
      "text": "of the bases."
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 854100.0,
      "end_time": 855767.0,
      "text": "If you had a big one   on this side you had"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 855767.0,
      "end_time": 859534.0,
      "text": "to have a particular small one   on this side or vice-versa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 859534.0,
      "end_time": 862234.0,
      "text": "and so on, all the way up."
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 862234.0,
      "end_time": 864367.0,
      "text": "So it meant that you   could easily make..."
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 864367.0,
      "end_time": 866601.0,
      "text": "by separating the two chains,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 866601.0,
      "end_time": 870234.0,
      "text": "you could then easily make   a new complementary copy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 870234.0,
      "end_time": 872033.0,
      "text": "by just obeying these   pairing rules"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 872033.0,
      "end_time": 873400.0,
      "text": "of which one went with what."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 873400.0,
      "end_time": 876100.0,
      "text": "And that solved in one   blow the whole idea"
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 876100.0,
      "end_time": 878167.0,
      "text": "of how you replicate a gene."
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 878167.0,
      "end_time": 881234.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] The structure   immediately revealed two things:"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 881234.0,
      "end_time": 883501.0,
      "text": "how genetic information   is stored,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 883501.0,
      "end_time": 887067.0,
      "text": "and how changes, or   mutations, happen."
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 887067.0,
      "end_time": 890734.0,
      "text": "The information is stored by   the sequence of the bases."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 890734.0,
      "end_time": 893200.0,
      "text": "Mutations occur when   the sequence is changed."
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 893200.0,
      "end_time": 895534.0,
      "text": "[WATSON:] It&#39;s a   simpler and better answer"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 895534.0,
      "end_time": 897667.0,
      "text": "than we&#39;d ever dared hope for."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 897667.0,
      "end_time": 901100.0,
      "text": "[CRICK:] I remember an   occasion when Jim gave a talk--"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 901100.0,
      "end_time": 903834.0,
      "text": "it&#39;s true they gave him one   or two drinks before dinner--"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 903834.0,
      "end_time": 906234.0,
      "text": "it was rather a short talk,   because all he could say"
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 906234.0,
      "end_time": 911634.0,
      "text": "at the end was, &quot;well, you see,   it&#39;s so pretty, it&#39;s so pretty.&quot;"
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 911634.0,
      "end_time": 914267.0,
      "text": "[WATSON:] I think everyone   just took joy in it"
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 914267.0,
      "end_time": 917634.0,
      "text": "because the field needed it."
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 917634.0,
      "end_time": 920767.0,
      "text": "But on the other hand,   you know [laughs],"
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 920767.0,
      "end_time": 923133.0,
      "text": "the Biochemistry   Department didn&#39;t invite us"
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 923133.0,
      "end_time": 925534.0,
      "text": "to give a seminar on it."
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 925534.0,
      "end_time": 928434.0,
      "text": "[CARROLL:] When the structure of   the double helix was revealed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 928434.0,
      "end_time": 932501.0,
      "text": "most biologists instantly   recognized the power"
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 932501.0,
      "end_time": 935033.0,
      "text": "of the explanation before them."
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 935033.0,
      "end_time": 937334.0,
      "text": "Here was this beautiful molecule"
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 937334.0,
      "end_time": 940400.0,
      "text": "that could explain both   the stability of life"
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 940400.0,
      "end_time": 947000.0,
      "text": "over huge amounts of time and   its mutability in evolution."
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 947000.0,
      "end_time": 949901.0,
      "text": "[JUDSON:] Their triumph was   reported in the journal Nature."
    },
    {
      "index": 317,
      "start_time": 949901.0,
      "end_time": 951701.0,
      "text": "It made headlines   around the world."
    },
    {
      "index": 318,
      "start_time": 951701.0,
      "end_time": 956801.0,
      "text": "And was celebrated nine years   later with a Nobel Prize."
    },
    {
      "index": 319,
      "start_time": 956801.0,
      "end_time": 959534.0,
      "text": "[LUGER:] That&#39;s kind of what   every scientist dreams about:"
    },
    {
      "index": 320,
      "start_time": 959534.0,
      "end_time": 963667.0,
      "text": "to make a discovery that   has this kind of impact."
    },
    {
      "index": 321,
      "start_time": 963667.0,
      "end_time": 966767.0,
      "text": "[CARROLL:] For biologists,   the discovery"
    },
    {
      "index": 322,
      "start_time": 966767.0,
      "end_time": 969834.0,
      "text": "of the double helix opened   up a whole new world."
    },
    {
      "index": 323,
      "start_time": 969834.0,
      "end_time": 973400.0,
      "text": "It was a passport to all   the mysteries of life,"
    },
    {
      "index": 324,
      "start_time": 973400.0,
      "end_time": 983400.0,
      "text": "mysteries that biologists   have been decoding ever since."
    }
  ]
}